    "biomes": ["forest"],
    "weight": 7,
    "one_shot": false,
    "text": "A low depression in the forest floor has become a slime breeding ground—thick, slow-moving, and audible from thirty feet away. Slimes don't usually colonize forests. Something is wrong with this soil.",
